)]">{ &quot;error&quot;: { error fields } }</code>. <strong class="font-bold">Note</strong>: <code class="py-[1px] px-1.5 min-w-[1.625rem] justify-center items-center ring-1 ring-inset ring-tint bg-tint rounded text-[.875em] leading-[calc(max(1.20em,1.25rem))]">tc_create_context</code> doesn&#x27;t store pointer passed in <code class="py-[1px] px-1.5 min-w-[1.625rem] justify-center items-center ring-1 ring-inset ring-tint bg-tint rounded text-[.875em] leading-[calc(max(1.20em,1.25rem))]">config</code> parameter. So it is safe to free this memory after the function returns.
